Generally you want to push changes to the devel / "master"/main  branch of upstream/master for git.bioconductor.org<http://secure-web.cisco.com/1ihijSvcMHCuleAbnELN6RSpgE3Mc0OYvJhtoRwlisGvSe07GKv92w97DSDYoZkBC8pRH5OxCj7vhHZTUjcTmbencSEm2s7ZOVYzL2WHu_yRomqdcpGug4aQNscYDF8yP-6SmFtP0Lf8VCnwEhdtr-KdtIuBBRc8sO-eCl0VZp0k6_XiAf5kit9svnxuWwpK1-epHjO824R2Mi5tiXpj8T3m689UXh8lh8668Avn5Z7j-vZ1RU68DcaiqdGqVvp7F4EiHhapK1YiJWK7G1g9f2OsbYws_ZFv0FOpBjle_I4L_rRp5X0_SsqpDkQs3guiV/http%3A%2F%2Fgit.bioconductor.org>.  We only encourage pushing to the RELEASE_X_Y  branch for bug corrections and not for enhancements or new features.  And you would also want to push any changes also to your gihub to make sure they stay in sync.

