There are a few issues.

I see the pushed changes but only on the master branch.  The email you received indicated it also was failing on the Release 3.12 (RELEASE_3_12) branch.

Please see the instructions for pushing to both release and devel branches of Bioconductor:

bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/git/bug-fix-in-release-and-devel/

Secondly,  Bioconductor will only propagate packages that have a valid version bump.  When you pushed your changes to the master (devel 3.13) branch. It did not include a valid version bump.  you need to bump the version to 1.1.1  in devel  ...

Please note. When you push the changes to release, you need to follow the versioning described here. So the version bump on that branch would be 1.0.1.

bioconductor.org/developers/how-to/version-numbering/


Hope this helps
Cheers,


